We have therefore shown that at each step, xt−1 ∼ q(xt−1|xt, x0) is normally distributed, with mean μq(xt, x0) that is a function of xt and x0, and variance Σq(t) as a function of α coefficients. These α coefficients are known and fixed at each timestep; they are either set permanently when modeled as hyperparameters, or treated as the current inference output of a network that seeks to model them. Following Equation 84, we can rewrite our variance equation as Σq(t) = σq2(t)I, where:
σ2
