(85)
In order to match approximate denoising transition step pθ(xt−1|xt) to ground-truth denoising transition step q(xt−1|xt, x0) as closely as possible, we can also model it as a Gaussian. Furthermore, as all α terms are known to be frozen at each timestep, we can immediately construct the variance of the approximate denoising transition step to also be Σq(t) = σq2(t)I. We must parameterize its mean μθ(xt, t) as a function of xt, however, since pθ(xt−1|xt) does not condition on x0.
